title: Mauboy to tell her story in TV drama
text:
Jessica Mauboy adds ‘flavour’ to Channel 7’s 2016 drama slate, starring in The Secret Daughter Holly Byrnes National TV writer News Corp Australia Network Jessica Mauboy adds ‘flavour’ to Channel 7’s 2016 drama slate, starring in The Secret Daughter Holly Byrnes National TV writer News Corp Australia Network Bran Nue Dae trailer 0:54 
Jessica Mauboy stars in this feature flick 'Bran Nue Dae' along side stars Geoffrey Rush, Ernie Dingo, Missy Higgins and Magda Szubanski. July 31st 2009 6 years ago /video/video.news.com.au/Entertainment/Movies/ 
POP princess Jessica Mauboy will share some of her own life story in a new Channel 7 drama series scripted especially for the singer’s TV drama debut. 
The Sapphires film star will play the lead role in The Secret Daughter , to launch next year — adding what she calls her own indigenous “flavour” to the part of a country pub singer who explores her family ties after a chance meeting with a city hotelier. 
The first season of 10 episodes will begin filming in Sydney in December, after the Sony Music songbird puts the finishing touches to her fourth studio album. Midas touch ... singer Jessica Mauboy will share her life story in television series The Secret Daughter. 
Mauboy will earn herself a producer credit for the Seven and Screentime/Banijay co-production, adding more sparkle to her already dazzling list of career credits. 
The Darwin-born beauty said the opportunity to create “new pathways” for young indigenous Australians was part of the appeal in committing to the TV project scripted around her. 
“I remember growing up and watching a lot of Austrlaian TV shows and there wasn’t a lot on it for me to believe, or to dream that this could be possible for me,” Mauboy told News Corp Australia. Other Stories
